16/03/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stjepan Mesic said on Saturday (March 15th) that Croatia can be ready to join the EU by 2010. 
In an interview with news agency Hina, the president said in order to achieve this success, the country must implement all reforms and pass legislation that would allow it to become a member of the Union. 
Asked about Croatia's position on Kosovo, Mesic said Zagreb will soon recognise the new country's independence. 
(Hina, Javno.com, Vecernji List - 15/03/08)
